# LLM Prompt Engineering Patterns

## Topic Context Injection
Screening and study-classifier prompts start with this context block, populated from ReviewConfig:
```
Role: {role from settings.yaml}
Goal: {goal with topic and research_question interpolated}
Backstory: {backstory with domain interpolated}
Topic: {topic}
Research Question: {research_question}
Domain: {domain}
Keywords: {keywords joined by comma}
```

Not all prompts use this block. Extraction (`extractor.py`) uses a structured extraction header
with intervention/population/outcome fields. HyDE (`hyde.py`) and the reranker (`reranker.py`)
use minimal one-line system prompts. Writing section prompts use a trimmed Role + Topic only.

## Structured Output Enforcement
All prompts end with:
"Return ONLY valid JSON matching this exact schema: {schema}"

## Truncation Limits (context window + cost control)
- Title/abstract screening: full title + abstract (no truncation)
- Full-text screening: first 8,000 characters of full text
- Data extraction: first 32,000 characters of full text (the pro-tier model supports a large context window; PDFs parsed with PyMuPDF via pdf_retrieval.py produce clean markdown up to ~60K chars)

## Confidence Thresholds (from config/settings.yaml)
- Auto-include if confidence >= stage1_include_threshold (0.85)
- Auto-exclude if confidence >= stage1_exclude_threshold (0.80)
- Papers between thresholds -> sent to adjudicator
- Adaptive calibration (calibrate_threshold=true in ScreeningConfig, default true) may override these defaults via bisection before the main screening loop; final adjusted thresholds are logged at phase_done for the screening_calibration phase

## Writing Grounding Block (WritingGroundingData)
Every writing section prompt includes a FACTUAL DATA BLOCK built by `format_grounding_block()` in
`src/writing/context_builder.py`. Key fields injected:
- PRISMA counts: total_identified, duplicates_removed, automation_excluded (BM25/keyword pre-filter),
  total_screened, fulltext_assessed, total_included
- records_after_deduplication: pre-computed (total_identified - duplicates_removed); injected verbatim
  with a CRITICAL note -- the LLM MUST use this value and MUST NOT subtract duplicates itself
- records_excluded_screening: pre-computed (total_screened - fulltext_assessed); same rationale --
  never let the LLM derive PRISMA arithmetic; all derived counts must be pre-computed and injected
- batch_screen_forwarded, batch_screen_excluded: populated when the batch LLM pre-ranker is active;
  used to emit the 3-stage funnel detail in the grounding block
- zero_yield_databases: databases searched with 0 records -- MUST be disclosed per PRISMA 2020 item 7
- cohens_kappa: when not None, instructs LLM to report exact value; when None, explicitly instructs
  LLM NOT to report a kappa value
- screening_method_description: injected verbatim; states that full-text PDFs were not retrieved
- VALID CITATION KEYS: includes both included study citekeys AND methodology citekeys
  (Page2021, Sterne2019, Sterne2016, Guyatt2011, Cohen1960) from register_methodology_citations()
